  <titleInfo>
    <title>1840 Jul. 16, Fountain Head, Tennessee [to] Adam Fergusson, Carthage, Tennessee / David Bradley</title>
  </titleInfo>
  <abstract>This is a letter from David Bradley to Adam Fergusson, dated July 16, 1840. Bradley writes that he has received the money that Fergusson sent him. He writes that he will not need to borrow any more unless his business is hindered, which he predicts would occur if elections produced a Whig government.</abstract>
